# Security rules

- **Never commit secrets.** `.env*` is gitignored (except `.env.example`). Don't
  log secrets.
- **Headers/CSP:** target a restrictive Content-Security-Policy + security
  headers (X-Frame-Options, X-Content-Type-Options, Referrer-Policy,
  Permissions-Policy). Currently missing — TD-001 (P1).
- **XSS:** rely on React escaping. `dangerouslySetInnerHTML` only for controlled,
  static content (JSON-LD, theme script) — never user input.
- **Validation:** validate/sanitize all external input server-side.
- **AuthZ:** least privilege; RBAC when auth is added.
- **Dependencies:** run `npm audit`; triage high/critical.
- Follow OWASP Top 10. Details: `.claude/CHECKLISTS/security.md`.
